The paper discusses the use of Constraint Programming (CP) approaches for sequential pattern mining (SPM), which involves both artificial intelligence (AI) and database (DB) techniques. The paper also mentions data mining (DM) and uses experiments to show the efficiency of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG). Finally, the paper discusses the modularity of CP approaches, which is a software engineering (SE) concept. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.DM, cs.LG, and cs.SE, in that order.
